PacketWyrm
==========

The PacketWyrm hardware design is licensed under the CERN Open Hardware
Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S-2.0); see LICENSE.

Why CERN-OHL-S: the Phase 2 SFP+ 10G data path reuses the Taxi
transceiver/Ethernet library (MAC, 10GBASE-R PCS, GTYE4), which is
CERN-OHL-S-2.0. That licence is strongly reciprocal, so the combined
design is distributed under the same terms.

Third-party components
----------------------

- Taxi (10G/25G Ethernet MAC, PCS, GTY; AS02MC04 board support)
  https://github.com/fpganinja/taxi  -- CERN-OHL-S-2.0,
  Copyright (c) FPGA Ninja, LLC. Included as a git submodule at
  rtl/phase2/vendor/taxi (see rtl/phase2/README.md). SPDX headers are
  retained in every Taxi source file.

- AS02MC04 pin assignments and SPI-flash boot configuration in
  fpga/as02mc04/xdc/ are derived from the Taxi AS02MC04 board support
  (CERN-OHL-S-2.0) and from Julia Desmazes' reverse-engineering work
  (https://essenceia.github.io/projects/alibaba_cloud_fpga/).

The host-side software under sw/ (libpacketwyrm, packetwyrmd, pktwyrm)
is a separate work; if you intend to distribute it under different
terms, keep it at arm's length from the CERN-OHL-S hardware sources.
